category: Libs
requires: cygwin libcorona1.0.2 libgcc1 libstdc++6
sdesc: "Image input/output library (utilities)"
ldesc: "Corona is an image input/output library that can read, write, and
manipulate image files in just a few lines of code. It can write PNG and TGA
files, and read PNG, JPEG, PCX, BMP, TGA, and GIF. Corona was designed to be
easy to use, and exports a straightforward C++ API. With just a few lines of
C++, you can add image loading to your application."
